132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1000
H.P. 647 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
An Act to Require Correctional Facilities and Substance Use
Disorder Treatment Facilities to Release Prisoners and Patients to a
Responsible Adult
Reference to the Committee on Health and Human Services suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CIMINO of Bridgton.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §20043, sub-§9 is enacted to read:
3 9. Discharge. Upon completion of a treatment program, the facility must ensure that
4 the person is discharged to the care of a responsible adult who the facility has determined
5 is able to support the person's adjustment to discharge from the treatment program.
6 Sec. 2. 34-A MRSA §3047, sub-§3, ¶D, as amended by PL 1991, c. 314, §52, is
7 further amended to read:
8 D. If the prisoner requests a reasonable place nearer the place of incarceration than
9 any of the foregoing the places in paragraphs A to C, transportation must be furnished
10 to that place; or
11 Sec. 3. 34-A MRSA §3047, sub-§4, as amended by PL 1991, c. 314, §52, is further
12 amended to read:
13 4. Extreme circumstances. May, in extreme circumstances, if the prisoner's home is
14 outside the State, or if the prisoner has secured employment outside the State, furnish
15 transportation to the prisoner's home or place of employment.; or
16 Sec. 4. 34-A MRSA §3047, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
17 5. Support from responsible adult. Shall ensure that the prisoner is released to the
18 care of a responsible adult who the commissioner has determined is able to support the
19 prisoner's transition from incarceration.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services to adopt rules to
2222 require a substance use disorder treatment facility to ensure that a patient is discharged to
2233 the care of a responsible adult as determined by the facility. The bill also requires the
2244 Commissioner of Corrections to ensure that, when a prisoner is released, the prisoner is
2255 released to the care of a responsible adult as determined by the commissioner.
